<project version="1.0" title="Orbit trap" domains="">
	<step title="">
		<instructions>&lt;p&gt;JAME supports orbit trap algorithms to render Mandelbrot and Julia sets. Open the configuration window to set the orbit trap.&lt;/p&gt;</instructions>
		<visual_media>screencapture 1205353407.png</visual_media>
		<annotations>
			<annotation style="line" lineSize="5" lineColor="255,0,0" opacity="100" startArrow="false" endArrow="true" arrowSize="6" points="120,403 172,450" />
		</annotations>
	</step>
	<step title="">
		<instructions>&lt;p&gt;Press edit layers button to modify the layers.&lt;/p&gt;</instructions>
		<visual_media>screencapture 1205353449.png</visual_media>
		<annotations>
			<annotation style="line" lineSize="5" lineColor="255,0,0" opacity="100" startArrow="false" endArrow="true" arrowSize="6" points="134,275 170,232" />
		</annotations>
	</step>
	<step title="">
		<instructions>&lt;p&gt;Press configure button of the Mandelbrot image layer.&lt;/p&gt;</instructions>
		<visual_media>screencapture 1205353459.png</visual_media>
		<annotations>
			<annotation style="line" lineSize="5" lineColor="255,0,0" opacity="100" startArrow="false" endArrow="true" arrowSize="6" points="668,239 706,190" />
		</annotations>
	</step>
	<step title="">
		<instructions>&lt;p&gt;The orbit trap defines the algorithm used to determine the convergence of an orbit point to the fractal attractor, so the result depends on the rendering formula and the transforming formula. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The first defines the formula used to calculate the orbit and the second defines the transformation applied to the complex plane points.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The processing formula finally defines the computation applied to every orbit point during orbit calculation, so it depends on the orbit trap because the trap influences the orbit. &lt;/p&gt;</instructions>
		<visual_media>screencapture 1205353478.png</visual_media>
		<annotations>
		</annotations>
	</step>
	<step title="">
		<instructions>&lt;p&gt;Select the processing formula Z Minimum. This formula assigns to a variable T the minimum value of the orbit point Z obtained from the rendering formula during orbit calculation. &lt;/p&gt;</instructions>
		<visual_media>screencapture 1205353489.png</visual_media>
		<annotations>
			<annotation style="line" lineSize="5" lineColor="255,0,0" opacity="100" startArrow="false" endArrow="true" arrowSize="6" points="176,253 221,212" />
		</annotations>
	</step>
	<step title="">
		<instructions>&lt;p&gt;Press outcolouring formulas button to modify the outcolouring formulas.&lt;/p&gt;</instructions>
		<visual_media>screencapture 1205353498.png</visual_media>
		<annotations>
			<annotation style="line" lineSize="5" lineColor="255,0,0" opacity="100" startArrow="false" endArrow="true" arrowSize="6" points="501,331 420,303" />
		</annotations>
	</step>
	<step title="">
		<instructions>&lt;p&gt;Select the T Modulus formula. This formula assigns to a point of the complex plane a color calculated from the modulus of the T variable obtained from the processing formula.&lt;/p&gt;</instructions>
		<visual_media>screencapture 1205353526.png</visual_media>
		<annotations>
			<annotation style="line" lineSize="5" lineColor="255,0,0" opacity="100" startArrow="false" endArrow="true" arrowSize="6" points="512,209 547,165" />
		</annotations>
	</step>
